parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature failure of headlight bulbs can lead to reduced visibility, increased risk of accidents, and potential safety hazards, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Headlight bulbs burning out frequently (every 4-6 months)
dim or low-beam headlights
inability to see the road ahead
having to replace bulbs multiple times
carrying spare bulbs
and experiencing safety concerns.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The frequent failure of the low beam headlights can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The low beam headlights burn out frequently
requiring replacement every 2-6 months
the headlights may turn off suddenly while driving
the bulbs may not function properly
the headlight assemblies may be damaged due to high electrical current.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight assembly and electrical components can cause the headlights to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The headlight assemblies may be damaged
the adapters and sockets may be burned
the fuses may be blown
the headlights may not function properly
the electrical system may be compromised.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle sensor can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle may stall or lose power
the throttle sensor may fail
the vehicle may jump forward or backward unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to failure to deploy in the event of a crash, resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the airbag system fails to deploy in a crash
the passenger seat airbag control sensor is defective
the airbag system makes a sound when no one is in the seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inability to obtain recall repairs for the airbag system can lead to continued risk of airbag failure, resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: Difficulty finding a dealership or repair center to perform the recall repair
long distances to travel for repair
lack of communication from the manufacturer or dealership
parts not available for repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Defective Passenger Seat Airbag Control Sensor
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective passenger seat airbag control sensor can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to failure to deploy in the event of a crash, resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag system fails to turn off the passenger side airbag for very light passengers
the airbag system makes a sound when no one is in the seat.
